Path rendering:

  Make jd__path_to_string public.
  Make it always generate a parseable path - quoting keys if necessary.

Path parsing:

  Make syntax stricter and test it.

UTF8

  jd_utf8_extract     // extract substr to uint32_t array
  jd_utf8_append      // splice in uint32_t chars
  jd_utf8_unpack      // string -> array of 32 bit chars
  jd_utf8_pack        // array -> string

  Under some circumstances it will be quicker to scan utf8 backwards
  from the end.

